        α
      
    
    {\displaystyle L_{\text{I}}\left(x_{0},\,\dots ,\,x_{n}\right)=\int _{S}x_{0}^{\alpha _{0}}\cdot \,\cdots \,\cdot x_{n}^{\alpha _{n}}\ \mathrm {d} \alpha }
  This can be simplified using divided differences of the exponential function to

  
    
      
        
